headline: MP Materials and the U.S. Department of War Partner with the Saudi Arabian Mining Company (Maaden) to Develop Rare Earth Refinery Joint Venture
summary: WASHINGTON, November 19, 2025--MP Materials Corp. (NYSE: MP), America’s fully-integrated rare earth materials and magnetics producer, today announced it has partnered with the U.S. Department of War (DoW) to establish a strategic joint venture with the Saudi Arabian Mining Company (Maaden), Saudi Arabia’s flagship mining company, to develop a rare earth refinery in the Kingdom. headline: Is GM’s Recent 32% Rally Justified After Its Electric Vehicle Partnerships?
summary: Curious if General Motors is actually a bargain right now? You are not alone, especially with so many big names making bold calls on the auto industry these days. The stock has been on a wild ride, up 16.4% over the past month and now sitting 32.2% higher year to date; though it did dip 4.6% in the last week. Recent headlines have spotlighted GM’s deeper push into electric vehicles and its high-stakes partnership announcements. Both of these factors have the market buzzing about future...
